original_title: Manhattan: Wadsworth Avenue - St. Nicholas Avenue
text:
Wadsworth Avenue, south from 193rd Street and St. Nicholas Avenue, at the northern end of Wadsworth Avenue. The building at the extreme left ("Soda"), at the S.E. corner of St. Nicholas Avenue and 193rd Street, and the convex-faced apartment house to the right of the picture, are the newest buildings, erected between 1922 and 1925. Beyond the latter, on the west side of Wadsworth Avenue, are three apartment buildings (Grand View, Ben Nevis, and Strathcona) built between 1910 and 1916, the first ones on this part of Wadsworth Avenue.

October 26, 1927.

P. L. Sperr.
